<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFEPICA_community_members2004">EPICA community members (2004-06-10). "<a href="http://www.up.ethz.ch/people/flueckiger/publications/epica04nat.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.up.ethz.ch/people/flueckiger/publications/epica04nat.pdf" rel="nofollow">Eight glacial cycles from an Antarctic ice core</a>" (PDF). <i>Nature</i> <b>429</b>: 623. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1038%2Fnature02599" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1038%2Fnature02599" rel="nofollow">10.1038/nature02599</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.up.ethz.ch/people/flueckiger/publications/epica04nat.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.up.ethz.ch/people/flueckiger/publications/epica04nat.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.up.ethz.ch/people/flueckiger/publications/epica04nat.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Eight+glacial+cycles+from+an+Antarctic+ice+core&amp;rft.jtitle=Nature&amp;rft.aulast=EPICA+community+members&amp;rft.au=EPICA+community+members&amp;rft.date=2004-06-10&amp;rft.volume=429&amp;rft.pages=623&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1038%2Fnature02599&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.up.ethz.ch%2Fpeople%2Fflueckiger%2Fpublications%2Fepica04nat.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ice_age"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-BergerLoutre-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-BergerLoutre_10-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/297/5585/1287" class="external text" title="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/297/5585/1287" rel="nofollow">"CLIMATE: An Exceptionally Long Interglacial Ahead?"</a>. Science. 2002<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/297/5585/1287" class="external free" title="http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/297/5585/1287" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/297/5585/1287</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-03-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CLIMATE%3A+An+Exceptionally+Long+Interglacial+Ahead%3F&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=Science&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencemag.org%2Fcgi%2Fcontent%2Ffull%2F297%2F5585%2F1287&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ice_age"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070829193436.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070829193436.htm" rel="nofollow">"Next Ice Age Delayed By Rising Carbon Dioxide Levels"</a>. ScienceDaily. 2007<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070829193436.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070829193436.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070829193436.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-02-28</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Next+Ice+Age+Delayed+By+Rising+Carbon+Dioxide+Levels&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pub=ScienceDaily&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2007%2F08%2F070829193436.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ice_age"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
